<TEXT>
former president ronald reagan received the ncaas 
highest award monday night but he wasnt a popular choice among 
some college administrators who felt he hurt womens athletics 
during his time in office 
president reagan did a lot of good things but it just happens 
he didnt dolopiano womens athletic director of the university of texas 
reagans record on womens athletics is abysmal he set it 
back 10 years he was also the worst education president in the 
last 40 years said lopiano 
there was no organized protest during the twohour award dinner 
but several women refused to stand with the rest of the crowd when 
reagan was introduced for the theodore roosevelt award 
the former presidnt made no reference to the controversy in his 
remarks to the audience of 2000 and joked nancy has my 
football sweater from eurek3ollege and wait until i come home 
with this 
earlier lopiano remarked that richard nixon would be a better 
choice he was president when title ix was promulgated 
congress passed title ix in 1972 forcing colleges and 
universities to provide equal opportunity to males and females at 
any school receiving federal funds the act appliel sainly to 
athletic programs 
in 1984 the supreme court tightened the language of the act in 
effmcj striking down title ix in regard to athletics since no 
athletic department received federal funds reagan supported the 
supreme courts decision 
the civil rights restoration act sponsored by us sen edward 
kennedy in 1988 brought back title ix in regard to athletics the 
act was passed by congress but vetoed by reagan congress 
however overrode his veto which restored the act 
former professional golfer carol mann resigned her seat on the 
awards committee in protest of the ncaas decision to honor reagan 
objecting to his opposition to title ix as it applied to athletics 
the theodore roosevelt award nicknamed the teddy award has 
been presented since 1967 and is given by the ncaa to a 
distinguished citizen of national reputation and outstanding 
accomplishment 
reagan hh resides in los angeles is a 1932 graduate of eureka 
college where he played football 
harry reasoner coeditor of 60 minutesgamppwas emcee for the 
ncaa honors dinner at the loews anatole hotel in dallas 
