the average price for a gallon of gasoline 
rose more than 45 cents during the past three weeks due mainly to 
a cold snap that slowed production an industry analyst said 
there was a supply curtailment because of the weather 
analyst trilby lundberg said sunday 
new taxes effective this month accounted for about onequarter 
cent of the overall increase said ms lundberg who heads the 
lundberg survey of nearly 5000 gasoline stations nationwide 
according to the survey the average price for gasoline as of 
friday was 11095 per gallon a 454 cent increase over the 
previous period 
the survey usually is issued every two weeks but took a oneweek 
break for the holidays 
for selfservice the average prices were regular unleaded 
9937 cents premium unleaded 11699 regular leaded 9806 cents 
for full service regular unleaded 12824 premium unleaded 
14162 regular leaded 12589 
</TEXT>
