<TEXT>
ford motor co will make frontseat air bags 
standard on its cars by the mid1990s the companys vice chairman 
said 
currently ford offers the safety devices and manual seat belts 
as standard on the driver side of about 1 million or half its 
ford lincoln and mercury cars 
passengerside air bags are offered in some lincolns 
all of our tests have shown that when the passenger is 
properly positioned with the active belt plus the use of the air 
bag provides the greatest protection in the event of an accident 
vice chairman harold poling said sunday night 
chrysler corp offers driverside air bags on all its north 
americanmade cars general motors corp has them standard on about 
500000 cars or about 15 percent gm has plans to more than double 
that number in the 1991 model year 
the federal government required that cars made after sept 1 
1989 be equipped with either a driverside air bag and manual seat 
belts for frontseat riders or automatic seat belts 
by 1993 automakers must supply passive restraint systems such 
as air bags or automatic belts for frontseat riders 
