bishops plan to formally charge newark bishop john s spong with 
violating the churchs doctrinal teachings 
a minimum of 10 bishops is needed to support a formal charge 
against a bishop wantland said he has far more than 10 
last month spong ordained gay deacon j robert williams into 
the priesthood at the all saints episcopal church in hoboken 
church traditionalists said spong violated a resolution of the 
churchs general convention that declares the ordination of a 
practicing homosexual to be inappropriate 
spong has said he considers the 1979 resolution adopted by the 
churchs governing body as advisory not church doctrine 
he noted that the resolution had been opposed by 20 bishops 
including presiding bishop edmond l browning 
in response to the planned charges spong said he welcomed any 
inquiry into his actions 
