will be selected by the end of this year but when asked when the 
tower would reopen replied we are talking about a few years 
i can promise that i will do all i can to hasten the 
reopening 
one plan which has been wellreceived by government experts 
calls for a wheelshaped support to be planted around the base of 
the tower the support would be connected by concrete spokes to the 
marble foundation 
the public works ministry is awaiting a report on soil 
conditions to decide whether the plan is feasible 
experts agree the tower must retain its famed lean and not be 
straightened 
