last months coup attempt was staged 
by more troops than previously thought and some senior officers 
believed most of the armed forces were involved in the plot 
according to documents obtained today 
the assessments were contained in sworn affidavits made to 
military investigators probing the bloody dec 19 attempt to 
topple president corazon aquino the associated press obtained 
copies of the statements from military sources 
in one affidavit a rebel army captain who later defected to the 
government said coup plotters had expected priests nuns 
government officials and civilians to join mutinous soldiers 
repeating the 1986 peoples power revolt that ousted the late 
ruler ferdinand marcos 
capt jose cruz assistant chief of staff of logistics for the 
philippine military said the failed coup that officials said left 
113 dead was launched to combat alleged corruption nepotism and 
inefficiency 
cruz and seven other military officers affirmed their statements 
friday before a government panel investigating whether to file 
rebellion charges against two retired brigadier generals implicated 
in the failed putsch 
