afghan rebels today claimed they 
killed 200 communist soldiers and repulsed hundreds more in a 
monthlong government assault on guerrilla positions in northwestern 
afghanistan 
the official rebel information agency midia said 70 rebels died 
in the fighting which also destroyed scores of homes in the 
district of shireen tagab about 75 miles south of afghanistans 
border with the soviet union 
the rebel agency blamed the destruction on indiscriminate 
bombing and shelling by government troops 
meanwhile midia said moscow sent two mig29 aircraft reportedly 
the latest in the soviet fleet of fighter jets to afghanistan 
along with a group of soviet pilots like most reports from both 
the rebels and the afghan government its authenticity could not be 
independently verified 
the pilots have been stationed in central afghanistans bagram 
airforce base the countrys largest midia said 
usbacked guerrilla fighters based in pakistan have been 
fighting for more than 11 years to topple successive communist 
governments in afghanistan until a year ago more than 103000 
soviet soldiers fought alongside afghan government troops 
