and the cable company violated the crossownership rule in effect 
since 1970 the commission ordered divestiture of the cable tv 
facilities in three communities within nitcos service area 
the us circuit court of appeals here upheld the commissions 
order last april after refusing to rule on nitcos constitutional 
challenge because it had not been raised before the commission 
northwest indiana catv last july sold the cable systems that 
were the subject of the commissions divestiture order 
the case is northwestern indiana telephone co vs fcc 89501 
