prices on the buenos aires stock 
exchange plunged an average of 53 percent in value monday when the 
market in economically wracked argentina reopened for the first 
time in more than a week 
meanwhile the government said inflation in december soared 40 
percent bringing the official 1989 rise in the cost of living to a 
record 4923 percent 
the two figures bode poorly for the government of president 
carlos menem which is implementing its fourth austerity plan since 
menem came to office in july and promised to sell off inefficient 
stateowned industries cut the burdensome budget deficit and 
steady the national currency 
but the austral the national currency slipped monday against 
the us dollar to 16501 down from 14001 last friday the 
austral which replaced the inflated peso traded at parity with 
the us dollar when the government of president raul alfonsin 
introduced it in 1986 
the sudden devaluation of the austral two weeks ago ignited the 
latest price hikes of 100 percent and more in most supermarket and 
department stores last february the austral traded at 171 
january inflation is expected to be at least 40 percent also 
said moises iconikoff planning secretary at the economy ministry 
analysts said the fall in stock prices the steepest in 
percentage since 1949 for the exchanges 16 major companies was in 
part because of the shortage of australs in circulation 
last week the governments latest economic team decreed a 
cutback in the amount of australs it would allow to be printed to 
reduce supplies of the national currency and force up the value of 
the austral 
economic indicators however continue to deteriorate real wages 
are about half their level of a year ago and investors continue to 
put their earnings in dollars a traditional haven for argentines 
in time of economic uncertainty total volume monday on the stock 
exchange as usual was low about 63 billion australs or 39 
million 
in an economy where inflation has been tripledigit in 14 of the 
last 15 years few people invest in stocks to protect their money 
and few companies count on the market to raise funds 
the market last open on dec 28 was closed two days for 
national holidays two days by bank holidays and two days by its 
board of directors which feared a selloff due to the austral 
shortage 
the independent news agency diarios y noticias said the stock 
market plunge of 53 percent was a historic session that had no 
precedent 
the board of business wholesalers in a statement said the 
economic situation was a crisis that is almost terminal and 
urged the government to cut the national budget deficit 
inflation in 1989 was the worst argentina has experienced since 
688 percent in 1984 
the economic convulsions are taking on political and social 
dimensions 
on friday telephone workers staged a demonstration in front of 
the state company entels headquarters to oppose the governments 
plan to sell the company 
the hopedfor sale of entel the state carrier aerolineas 
argentinas the state railroad and other moneylosing public 
companies is the heart of menems plans to steady argentinas 
economic situation 
meanwhile critics said the latest stabilization plan will 
exacerbate an existing recession and the low level of wages might 
touch off food riots and social unrest such unrest convulsed this 
country in may and june 
the intention to combat hyperinflation with hypermonetarism 
will only end in hyperrecession predicted national deputy jesus 
rodriguez who served briefly as economy minister during the 
198389 radical civic union government of alfonsin 
alfonsins election ended the militarys nearly sevenyear reign 
the military has intervened six times since 1930 to cut short 
argentine governments 
