<TEXT>
if its love letters it must be lynn 
redgrave or was it colleen dewhurst elaine stritch swoosie kurtz 
or stockard channing and was she joined by richard thomas jason 
robards christopher reeve or cliff robertson 
a different cast starred each week in the ar gurney play on 
and offbroadway an idea its producers hope to continue as the 
twocharacter comedydrama multiplies in other productions across 
the country and perhaps heads for london later this year 
more than 60 performers appeared in the play during its new york 
run that began last valentines day at a special benefit 
performance starring kathleen turner and john rubinstein and ends 
today after a 3month engagement at broadways edison theater in 
between there were twiceweekly performances at the promenade 
theater offbroadway that later became eight shows a week before 
the move to the edison 
but its not the end for the play which looks at a man and 
woman two upperclass wasps through their letters to each other 
from the ages of 7 until they are about 60 
a company is now playing in san francisco where the actors 
rotate every two weeks among the performers playing there have 
been polly bergen robert vaughn alexis smith and fritz weaver 
another troupe opens in boston on feb 20 for seven weeks with 
seven different casts 
also in february love letters will be performed sundays 
and mondays at the pasadena playhouse in california with a regular 
run scheduled to start in a los angeles theater in midmarch 
a chicago company is also under discussion as is a national 
tour in the fall richard frankel who produced the play with roger 
l stevens thomas viertel and steven baruch describes that as 
unique 
were going to be booking the show into normal broadway road 
houses he says for example we might do two weeks at the 
kennedy center or two weeks in philadelphia or a week in lexington 
ky but they wont necessarily be continuous and they might be 
overlapping and they almost certainly will be with different 
actors 
it would be an unconventional tour for an unconventional play 
that playwright gurney insists must be read not acted by its 
stars 
these are two lovers who communicate through their letters 
gurney says they are both liberated and trapped in their own 
mail when they get together physically with one exception its 
normally bad the letters are the windows through which they wave 
at each other 
the play can be performed almost anywhere it requires no 
scenery and only a few props a table two chairs two small 
lecterns a water pitcher and two glasses the actors even wear 
their own clothes 
love letters was first done at the new york public library 
in march 1988 with holland taylor and gurney himself reading the 
play 
i was supposed to make a speech at the library but told them i 
wanted to do the play instead he recalls since it runs longer 
than a speech i broke it into two parts and told everybody they 
could leave if they wanted to nobody seemed to want to so i knew 
the play interested people 
if the show has a minimum of props it has required a maximum of 
effort behind the scenes to cast each week 
the hardest part of the new york production was that it was 
like an opening every week says frankel linda wright works for 
frankel as an assistant but she took over casting chores for the 
new york run as well as the outoftown assignments 
the most difficult thing is getting the right people 
together she says you cant do it with a much older man and a 
much younger woman these people supposedly went to school 
together 
originally most of the new york casts were in their early 40s 
and stretched into their 50s but it has been done successfully by 
younger actors such as timothy hutton and elizabeth mcgovern 
the actors all got the same amount of rehearsal time one 
threehour afternoon session in frankels office with director john 
tillinger going over the play tillinger read through the play with 
the newcomers each week 
the two stars dont have approval of their other halves 
frankel says sometimes we start with a pair we approach them 
both at the same time sometimes well talk to one person and they 
will suggest partners its a friendly negotiation process 
john rubinstein had never met stockard channing before they did 
love letters he had done the show before with joanna gleason 
channing had performed it with bruce davison they both had other 
commitments and arrived at the theater 40 minutes before the 
curtain went up 
they barely had time to say hello before going to work 
frankel says 
a few husbands and wives also have done the play among them 
nancy marchand and paul sparer as well as lynn redgrave and john 
clark 
word is now out among the acting community about what an 
excellent showcase love letters can be for a performer 
actors like to do it because its a good way for producers and 
agents to get a look at what they can do frankel says 
the commitment for only a week appeals to many performers who 
have family or longrange show business commitments 
some of the actors have appeared in different cities and may 
work again on the various tours robert vaughn and polly bergen did 
it in san francisco and then did it in new york lynn redgrave and 
john clark having performed the play in new york also will work 
in san francisco 
the thought of doing material this good and not having to 
learn it was fabulous redgrave says plus the play was 
something that my husband and i could do together after all these 
years we havent acted together since we met 23 years ago 
frankel insists the play stays remarkably the same even with its 
different performers 
because it is a new cast every week who are directed by the 
same director i think it has strayed less than a normal show does 
during a long run he says there is someone going back to the 
book every week instructing the actors how it is to be done 
having said that the show is totally different with different 
people doing it liz mcgovern and timothy hutton will be different 
from jason robards and colleen dewhurst everybody brings their own 
experience to it 
by the time love letters finishes its journey around the 
country there will be a lot of alumni the new york alumni already 
have a souvenir each received a very preppy crew neck sweater for 
their weeks work 
</TEXT>
