<TEXT>
private schools often packed with 50 students to a classroom 
lack desks chairs blackboards and chalk rarely do all students 
get the same editions of textbooks if they are available 
still private school tuition shot up 524 percent from january 
to june last year three times faster than the inflation rate 
students across the country held protest marches and tv news 
reports almost nightly showed riot troops clashing with teenagers 
spiraling tuition costs have led to an exodus of students from 
private to public schools further straining the system 
in rio de janeiros upper middleclass flamengo district half 
of the oncereputable amaro cavalcanti high school building was 
condemned because of cracked walls and ceilings electrical 
failure rats in classrooms and broken stairways said angela 
blemiro the public schools principal however classes are still 
held there 
