<TEXT>
saints martyrs and spirits have been brought to 
life as chinas leaders try to teach their people to be good 
communists in these times of sinking fortunes for communism around 
the world 
the role model selfless hardworking plainliving and loyal 
unto death is a timehonored educational tool in communist china 
now as chinas hardline leaders seek absolute allegiance to a 
system where absolutes no longer exist the party has again called 
on its paragons to lead the way 
they are a counterweight both to the antiparty prowest 
sentiments of the crushed prodemocracy movement of tiananmen 
square last spring and the political changes that have swept 
eastern europe 
some like perfect soldier lei feng perennially return at times 
of ideological strife others such as the young martyr lai ning 
are newcomers to the party pantheon 
there are also ideals such as the spirit of yanan that 
hark back to a simpler day when party leaders sought to serve 
rather than corrupt and young people dedicated lives to socialist 
idealism rather than western materialism 
these are a few of the legends now in vogue 
lei feng 
nearly two decades after his death chinese today offer blood 
sweep streets and give free haircuts in the name of peasant soldier 
lei feng 
lei who according to a childrens song walks 1000 miles and 
does 1000 good deeds was killed in 1962 at age 22 when he 
backed his truck into a utility pole but a year later chairman mao 
tsetung proclaimed him a communist saint in the first of many 
campaigns titled learn from lei feng 
according to legend the fervent patriot secretly washed the 
clothes of his comrades donated his savings to help peasants hit 
by floods and once gave his coat to a woman and her child during a 
freezing rainstorm 
for his latest reincarnation the peoples liberation army has 
distributed 300000 copies of his diary with a view to launching 
a new upsurge in the army on learning from lei feng 
the pla daily newspaper of the peoples liberation army said 
some supporters of degenerate western bourgeois concepts have 
tried to denigrate lei by saying hes outdated but it added if 
all soldiers can be like lei feng have unparalleled loyalty to the 
party and the people and give matchless love to socialism then 
our army will become an indestructible steel great wall 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
lai ning 
he died at age 14 in 1988 while trying to put out a forest fire 
near his home in northern china this past october he headed a list 
of the nations 10 best young pioneers a partyled youth 
organization and was described by the partys official newspaper 
peoples daily as a flaming torch of revolutionary spirit 
among the attributes praised about lai is one that he hoped to 
be a geologist so he could excavate precious metals from mountains 
around his home and contribute to our motherland 
study the hero lai ning meetings are being held across the 
country the city of beijing has issued a book the heroic youth 
lai ning and has organized study lai ning detachments in 
schools 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
model workers 
last fall 2000 model workers were assembled at the great hall 
of the people for the first national ceremony in three decades to 
honor such exemplars of labor 
the official press meanwhile is filled with tales such as the 
one of sweeper uncle jiang daoping a retired colonel and war 
hero who shot down seven enemy planes in the korean war but took a 
job as a janitor at shanghais tongji university after retiring 
his daughter worried she couldnt get a boyfriend with her 
father in such a lowly position tried to dissuade him but jiang 
reportedly replied it is no shame to do whatever i can for the 
society it will benefit both my body and soul 
then there is flying li songzhi a policewoman who at 52 
still leads a task force against pickpockets 
riding the bicycle at full speed i can keep up with a bus 
when a thief is riding on it she is quoted as saying in so 
doing i feel that i have regained my youth 
another is qiu tiandao a young army medic who reputedly is so 
skilled at acupuncture that he uses both hands to stick needles in 
two patients at the same time 
its my happiest thing to see the sufferings of the patients 
eased under my hands 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
learn from daqing 
this common call during the ultraleftist 196676 cultural 
revolution refers to the perseverance of those who built the 
