<TEXT>
the spirit of yanan 
yanan in the dusty hills of northwestern china was mao 
tsetungs revolutionary base for 13 years in the 1930s and 1940s 
when the red army was fighting the japanese as well as chiang 
kaisheks nationalists 
young chinese are now told to emulate the spirit of those days 
when mao and the other communist leaders lived in caves and worked 
among the yanan peasants 
the yanan spirit is the national treasure of the chinese 
