<TEXT>
the new inflationproofing of the tax 
system means a slightly lower burden for most taxpayers 
a single person with taxable income after deductions and 
exemptions of 29000 for example would have owed 5807 in tax 
without the annual inflation adjustment to the tax brackets 
instead the bill will be 5716 a saving of 2 percent 
a couple filing a joint return with 35000 taxable income will 
owe 5784 for 1989 3 percent less than the 5940 liability they 
would have faced without the inflation adjustment 
the adjustment was made by taxing an additional 4 percent of 
income at a lower rate 
for example the top of the lowest bracket 15 percent which 
is the only rate paid by about 8 of every 10 taxpayers was raised 
for joint returns from 29750 for 1988 to 30950 for 1989 for 
single people the 15 percent rate applies to 18550 of 1989 
taxable income up from 17850 in 1988 
in addition to the savings associated with widening the tax 
brackets taxpayers also are paying less because the personal 
exemptions have been increased and the standard deductions have 
been indexed to offset inflation 
the changes were voted as part of the tax overhaul enacted in 
1986 
</TEXT>
