1989 if you were 70 or older at yearend 
to determine your eligibility for a deductible contribution two 
figures are important 
the first is your modified adjusted gross income if you are 
filing form 1040a that means wages salaries and tips line 7 
for 1040 it means total income minus the adjustments on lines 26 
through 29 
the second figure is the phaseout level for a single person or 
unmarried head of household this is 35000 for a couple filing 
jointly it is 50000 for a married person filing a separate 
