looked forward to the next communication from jeff reynolds but 
added that so far the proposal was lacking in detail 
on saturday reynolds 28 announced in los angeles that he was 
prepared to invest 250 million in bond corp and in return take 
control of the company whose australian brewing interests are now 
in the hands of receivers bond corp also owns g heileman brewing 
co of la crosse wis 
he said he was confident he could refinance the companys 6 
billion debt and would talk again with millionaire businessman alan 
bond who has controlling interest in bond corp once the 
victorian supreme court hearing into the receivership is over 
in a telephone interview sunday in houston reynolds said he 
planned to travel to perth in coming weeks to discuss details of 
the bid with bond 
im scheduled to go back over to perth shortly to work out 
definitive agreements reynolds said this is something weve 
been working on since september 
