<TEXT>
tandem computers on monday announced a 
new computer that uses unix a standard operating system for 
controlling internal housekeeping functions of computers 
tandems action along with similar announcements expected 
monday from two other influential silicon valley companies signals 
a key trend in the computer industry toward the use of unix 
analysts said 
unix allows customers to avoid being locked into buying 
proprietary hardware and software available from just one vendor 
tandem the cupertinobased company known for reliable 
nonstop computers introduced its new integrity s2 system 
which will cost from 172000 to 248000 capable of performing 12 
million instructions per second it is based on the r2000 chip from 
mips computer systems and has three separate processors allowing 
it to keep running if one fails 
buyers have tended to balk at using unixbased systems for 
mainstream business purposes because they couldnt count on the 
systems being up and running said jeffrey beeler an analyst at 
dataquest it appears that tandem has done the best job of 
addressing reliability problems 
the other two companies are hewlettpackard co and intel corp 
in addition sunnyvalebased maspar computer corp planned to debut 
a new class of machine tuesday that approximates the power of a 
multimilliondollar supercomputer at a fraction of the price 
palo altobased hewlettpackard was expected to unveil two 
computer workstations that use a new version of a motorola 
microprocessor chip to perform 12 million instructions per second 
for a 50 percent increase for the hp product line the desktop 
model will start at 8995 
intel the santa clarabased company widely known for 
microprocessor chips is introducing new machines that can have 
from eight to 128 processors but they can get hefty speed boosts 
from the powerful i860 microprocessor from intels 80386 used in 
personal computers 
the systems range from 265000 to more than 1 million the 
largest configuration can perform 76 billion operations per second 
maspar one of the bestfunded computer startups in recent 
silicon valley history was scheduled to unveil its mp1 system a 
box 55 inches high and 23 inches wide attached to a digital 
microvax computer that can perform up to 15 billion calculations 
per second all for 170000 to 810000 
the intel and maspar machines link independent processing units 
together to address problems resulting in tremendous speed 
similar machines have been used to help design nuclear weapons 
and break codes and others are already used for financial analysis 
on wall street some observers expect them to become an important 
force in commercial computing 
the maspar and intel machines represent the new wave in 
computing said gary smaby an independent computer analyst in 
minneapolis 
