an art teacher said she had begun to detect 
a great deal of sexual and moral confusion in the minds of her 
students over what they had seen on tv 
her main target was the publicly financed bbc nearly a 
halfmillion people signed a petition in 1964 calling for closure 
of the bbc accusing it of broadcasting propaganda of disbelief 
doubt and dirt 
the bbc stayed on the air and barred mrs whitehouse from its 
programs for 15 years its directorgeneral at the time sir hugh 
greene said years later that her only contribution had been to 
raise the national level of intolerance 
critics still accuse her of trying to be the nations censor 
young people are not driven to excesses by explicit scenes of 
sex on the screen shes a very sincere lady but one of the most 
misguided said harry turner managing director of television 
south west an independent company 
mrs whitehouse insists her only demand is that broadcasters 
fulfill their responsibility not to offend against good taste and 
decency or incite crime 
it isnt that ones against sex or showing on tv that men and 
women love each other but its the kind of closeup voyeurism that 
people are sick and tired of she said 
her speeches draw capacity audiences and with influential 
figures such as mrs thatcher speaking out against overly explicit 
tv mrs whitehouse has come closer to representing mainstream 
british values 
