grand metropolitan plc seeking to turn 
burger king into a major international brand said monday it plans 
to buy 20 wimpy franchised restaurants in the united kingdom and 
convert them to burger king outlets 
the british food and liquor conglomerate which owns the 
minneapolisbased pillsbury co also said monday that it has met 
with a number of parties over the possible sale of its brewing 
interests although it also is considering other options to meet 
government antitrust recommendations 
in announcing the wimpy restaurants purchase from allied 
leisure plc london grand met said the sale was scheduled for 
completion jan 29 it did not disclose terms of the deal 
these 20 prime locations in london and the south coast of 
england will significantly strengthen our planned expansion of the 
burger king brand in the united kingdom said ian a martin 
chief executive of grand metropolitans us operations and 
chairman of the burger king subsidiary 
following our acquisition of ub restaurants in october 1989 
which included more than 800 restaurants in the united kingdom and 
europe this is the latest step in our strategy to build burger 
king as a major international brand martin said 
in the past three months burger king has doubled the number of 
its outlets in the united kingdom and now operates 60 restaurants 
there these include 23 former wimpy counter service outlets which 
were purchased as part of the ub restaurants acquisition burger 
king anticipates having over 200 owned or franchised outlets in the 
united kingdom by the end of 1990 
burger king operates approximately 6000 restaurants worldwide 
including more than 5400 in the united states 
regarding its brewing interests grand met which has 5000 
public houses said it was trying to determine how to meet 
recommendations of last years monopolies and mergers commission 
report which said brewers should be allowed to operate only 2000 
public houses or pubs 
but selling our brewing interests is only one option and no 
decisions have yet been made the company said 
grand met said it has held discussions with a number of 
companys which might lead to asset sales including courage ltd 
the british brewer owned by elders ixl of australia 
it is rumored that a potential deal with courage may involve the 
company swapping some of its public houses for grand mets brewing 
interests 
grand met brews a number of brands under license for a range of 
international companies including elders fosters lager 
grand met last year bought pillsbury which owned burger king 
in a deal valued at 575 billion 
in addition to burger king and pillsbury grand mets usbased 
subsidiaries include haagendazs alpo carillon heublein 
paddington and pearle 
