<TEXT>
jefferson smurfit corp the leading recycler 
of waste paper and waste management of north america inc on 
monday announced a joint venture to process and market recycled 
paper fiber 
a major obstacle to the successful recovery of paper fiber 
from the nations waste stream has been our inability to find 
stable markets and consistent demand for this valuable material 
said william p hulligan president of waste management of north 
america the largest provider of recycling collection services in 
the united states and canada 
hulligan said that waste managements collection systems 
facilities and technologies should result in greater efficiency and 
a constant source of raw material for customers 
the companies have signed a letter of intent to form smurfitwmi 
recycling co based in st louis 
under the agreement jefferson smurfits reclamation division 
would become an independent business owned equally by jefferson 
smurfit and waste management of north america a subsidiary of 
waste management inc of oak brook ill 
the company will sell reclaimed paper fiber to jefferson smurfit 
and its affiliates as well as other paper and paperboard mills for 
use in new paper products 
st louisbased jefferson smurfit is one of the largest paper 
and paperboard packaging companies in the united states its 
reclamation division has 32 processing plants and markets more than 
37 million tons a year of corrugated containers old newsprint and 
other products 
waste management of north america provides residential 
collection of recyclables from more than 12 million homes through 
contracts with 142 municipalities 
the companys recycle america and recycle canada residential and 
commercial programs collect more than 750000 tons of recyclable 
materials a year through more than 315 divisions in north american 
it operates 35 processing plants across the country in addition to 
paper the company recovers aluminum glass and plastics 
the new company will continue to operate jefferson smurfit 
recycling centers and market other recycled commodities waste 
management will provide corrugated newsprint and other papers 
recovered through its collection programs 
