<TEXT>
a mixed ruling from a federal appeals court 
over a landmark smokerdeath case drew a twopart chorus of victory 
monday from tobacco companies and a man who claims cigarettes 
killed his wife 
the 3rd us circuit court of appeals on friday overturned the 
nations first money damages judgment against the tobacco industry 
removing the only blemish from their nearly 40 years of victory in 
such cases 
but the panel also sent back for trial a reshaped case that will 
likely put smoking itself in the dock reinstated claims against 
two other tobacco companies and perhaps deepened the well for 
potential damages 
despite the outcome the decision adds perhaps years more of 
legal wrangling in a 7yearold case 
for this case its the lawyers unemployment act said 
